- A segment on y = 4x from x = a to x = b has length √17 (b − a).
- The portions under y = 10π sin^2 x occur where 4x ≤ 10π sin^2 x, i.e., sin^2 x ≥ 2x/(5π). The intersection points satisfy 4x = 10π sin^2 x, i.e., sin^2 x = 2x/(5π). These points in [0, 5π/2] come in symmetric pairs about 5π/4.
- Hence the total horizontal measure of these portions is 5π/4, so the total length is √17 · (5π/4) = 5π√17/4. \boxed{\frac{5\pi\sqrt{17}}{4}}
